request context for downstream handlers.\n  Line 641: │   Client    │────▶│  PicoD HTTP  │────▶│ JWT Middle- │────▶│   Handler   │\n  Line 642: │  (with JWT) │     │   Server     │     │   ware      │     │  (Business) │\n  Line 652: │   ├── validator.go       # JWT validation logic\n  Line 662: - `github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v5` - JWT parsing and validation\n  Line 677:     // SkipPaths are paths that bypass JWT validation\n  Line 749: 3. Parse and validate JWT\n  Line 775: | `JWT_MISSING` | 401 | No token provided |\n  Line 776: | `JWT_INVALID` | 401 | Token format/structure invalid |\n  Line 777: | `JWT_EXPIRED` | 401 | Token has expired |\n  Line 778: | `JWT_SIGNATURE_INVALID` | 401 | Signature verification failed |\n  Line 779: | `JWT_EXPIRY_EXCEEDED` | 401 | Token expiry exceeds maximum allowed |\n  Line 873: | Missing token | 401 | `{\"code\":\"JWT_MISSING\",\"message\":\"Authorization token required\"}` |\n  Line 874: | Invalid format | 401 | `{\"code\":\"JWT_INVALID\",\"message\":\"Invalid token format\"}` |\n  Line 875: | Expired token | 401 | `{\"code\":\"JWT_EXPIRED\",\"message\":\"Token has expired\"}` |\n  Line 876: | Bad signature | 401 | `{\"code\":\"JWT_SIGNATURE_INVALID\",\"message\":\"Invalid token signature\"}` |\n  Line 877: | Expiry exceeded | 401 | `{\"code\":\"JWT_EXPIRY_EXCEEDED\",\"message\":\"Token expiry exceeds maximum allowed\"}` |\n  Line 917: // GenerateTestToken creates a signed JWT for testing\n  Line 923: // NewTestRequest creates an HTTP request with optional JWT\n  Line 933: - TestFullRequestFlow_WithValidJWT\n  Line 934: - TestFullRequestFlow_WithExpiredJWT\n  Line 935: - TestFullRequestFlow_WithoutJWT\n  Line 980: | `PICOD_JWT_SIGNING_KEY` | Yes | - | Secret key for HMAC verification |\n  Line 981: | `PICOD_JWT_SIGNING_METHOD` | No | `HS256` | Signing algorithm (HS256, HS384, HS512) |\n  Line 982: | `PICOD_JWT_SKIP_PATHS` | No | - | Comma-separated list of paths to skip |\n  Line 983: | `PICOD_JWT_TOKEN_LOOKUP` | No | `header:Authorization` | Token extraction location |\n  Line 984: | `PICOD_JWT_EXPIRY_MAX` | No | `24h` | Maximum allowed token expiry duration |\n  Line 993: ├── validator.go       # JWT validation logic\n\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/.sdd_prompt.md:\n  Line 3: AR: AR-017 — PicoD JWT 中间件\n\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/AR-017-proposal.md:\n  Line 1: # AR-017: PicoD JWT Middleware\n  Line 5: This proposal implements JWT (JSON Web Token) authentication middleware for the PicoD HTTP daemon in the `pkg/picod` module. The goal is to:\n  Line 7: 1. **Secure API Access** - Protect PicoD HTTP endpoints with RSA-based JWT authentication\n  Line 8: 2. **Token Validation** - Validate JWT tokens signed with RSA private keys using the corresponding public key\n  Line 11: 5. **Health Endpoint Protection** - Optionally protect the health check endpoint with JWT authentication\n  Line 24:   - JWT middleware implementation (`middleware.go`)\n  Line 25:   - JWT token validation logic (`jwt.go`)\n  Line 33:   - JWT token generation (handled by external auth service)\n  Line 68: 2. **No JWT validation** - Cannot validate JWT tokens from incoming requests\n  Line 77: - Exposes health endpoint with JWT (RSA)-protected APIs\n  Line 80: - Authentication modes: `picod` (JWT required) or `none` (no auth)\n  Line 92: ### 1. JWT Middleware (`middleware.go`)\n  Line 95: // JWTMiddleware is HTTP middleware that validates JWT tokens\n  Line 96: type JWTMiddleware struct {\n  Line 107: // NewJWTMiddleware creates a new JWT middleware\n  Line 108: func NewJWTMiddleware(publicKey *rsa.PublicKey, skipPaths ...string) *JWTMiddleware\n  Line 111: func (m *JWTMiddleware) Middleware(next http.Handler) http.Handler\n  Line 113: // extractToken extracts the JWT token from the Authorization header\n  Line 114: func (m *JWTMiddleware) extractToken(r *http.Request) (string, error)\n  Line 117: func (m *JWTMiddleware) shouldSkip(path string) bool\n  Line 120: ### 2. JWT Validation (`jwt.go`)\n  Line 123: // Claims represents JWT token claims\n  Line 145: // Validate validates the JWT claims\n  Line 148: // ParseAndValidate parses and validates a JWT token\n  Line 151: // VerifySignature verifies the JWT signature\n  Line 245: // SetupHTTPServer creates the HTTP server with JWT middleware\n  Line 256:     // Apply JWT middleware\n  Line 264:         middleware := NewJWTMiddleware(publicKey, config.SkipPaths...)\n  Line 294: 1. **PicoD HTTP Server** (`code-execution/`): Will integrate JWT middleware into HTTP server setup\n  Line 297: 4. **Authentication Service** (external): Will generate JWT tokens for clients\n  Line 298: 5. **Client Applications**: Will include JWT tokens in `Authorization: Bearer <token>` header\n  Line 320: ### Alternative 1: Use Existing JWT Library (e.g., golang-jwt/jwt)\n  Line 335: **Decision**: Use a minimal custom implementation for simplicity and control, but structure code to easily swap in `golang-jwt/jwt` if needed. The custom implementation will follow JWT standards (RFC 7519) for compatibility.\n  Line 352: **Decision**: Use RSA-based JWT for deployment flexibility and simpler validation. PicoD should work both inside and outside Kubernetes.\n  Line 369: **Decision**: Use JWT for simpler token-based authentication. mTLS is better suited for service-to-service communication at the infrastructure level.\n  Line 386: **Decision**: Use JWT with RSA signatures for better security, standard claims, and asymmetric key distribution.\n  Line 392: 1. **TestJWTMiddleware_ValidToken**: Valid JWT token passes through\n  Line 393: 2. **TestJWTMiddleware_MissingToken**: Missing token returns 401\n\n(Results truncated: showing 100 of 357 matches (257 hidden). Consider using a more specific path or pattern.)","metadata":{"matches":357,"truncated":true},"title":"AR-017|picod.*middleware|JWT","time":{"start":1775862300351,"end":1775862300365}}}}
